<p></p><div style="text-align: center;"> <img src="http://29th.org/images/116thicon.gif" alt="header" /></div>

<h4>29TH INFANTRY DIVISION</h4>

<h4>116TH REGIMENT, 1ST BN</h4>

<h4>LIGHTHOUSE OFFICE</h4>

<p><br /></p>

<p>Thank you for enlisting with the 29th Infantry Division. Your application has been accepted and the next step in becoming a member is to complete <em>Basic Combat Training</em>.</p>

<h3>Your Basic Combat Training (BCT) Schedule:</h3>

<h5> <strong><span style="color:black;">When: </span></strong> </h5>

<p>Sunday 09 Aug 2015 through Thursday 13 Aug 2015, each night at 2pm EST</p>

<h5> <strong><span style="color:black;">Server: </span></strong> </h5>

<p>29th Infantry Division [Platoon Server] (192.223.31.16:2302)</p>

<h5> <strong><span style="color:black;">Password: </span></strong> </h5>

<p>29tha3</p>

<p><br /><em>While we understand if you have to miss a training session, your attendance is a significant factor in graduating BCT.</em></p>

<p>Join the <a rel="nofollow" href="http://steamcommunity.com/groups/29th647"><span style="color:blue;">Steam Friends Group</span></a> to receive reminders before your training starts</p>

<p><br /></p>

<h5> <strong><span style="color:black;">Important:</span></strong> </h5>

<p>Before you do <em>anything</em>, read the <a rel="nofollow" href="http://29th.org/handbook"><span style="color:blue;">Recruit Handbook</span></a> to learn what you will need to know to pass BCT. It also contains the basic 29th rules, Frequently Asked Questions and a guide on how to set your in-game name properly.</p>

<p>You may change your in-game name to: <strong>Pvt. Chamberlain [29th 647]</strong></p>

<p><br /></p>

<h5> <strong><span style="color:black;">Please note the following rules:</span></strong> </h5>

<ol>
<li><p>As a recruit you will train with the Rifleman Class only.<br />
<br /> <em>You are to use the Rifleman Class only on our servers, at all time.<br />
After you pass BCT you will have the opportunity to train with other weapons</em>.</p></li>
<li><p>Salute officers (and only officers) when they enter/leave our server.<br />
<br /> <em>&#42;Salute* ranks 2Lt, 1Lt, Cpt, Maj, Lt. Col. - See the <a rel="nofollow" href="http://29th.org/handbook"><span style="color:blue;">Recruit Handbook</span></a> for info on how to bind a key to salute.</em></p></li>
<li>Reply to this enlistment thread stating simply 'Checking In'.<br />
<br /> <em>This will let us know you are aware of your schedule so that we can put you on the training roster.</em><br />
<br /></li>
</ol>

<p><br />If you have any questions or concerns, please contact the following members, as they are here for you:<br />
<strong>T/5 Tuomainen</strong>: <a rel="nofollow" href="http://steamcommunity.com/id/tman29th/">Steam Profile</a> | <a rel="nofollow" href="http://forums.29th.org/messages/add/T5%20Tuomainen">Send a Private Message</a></p>

<p><br /><br /><br />
Please keep active on our server and forums, and good luck in basic.<br />
<br /><br /></p>

<p><img src="http://www.29th.org/sigs/76561197970174462.png" alt="sig" /><br />
<em>29th Infantry Division<br />
Lighthouse Corps<br />
Senior Enlistment Liaison</em></p>

